There are delays and service changes in 7 and 7 express service in both directions between Manhattan and Queens because of a person on the tracks being struck by a train at Grand Central-42 St.

There is no 7 train service in either direction between 34 St-Hudson Yards and Hunters Point Av. 
There is reduced 7 train service between Hunters Point Av and Flushing-Main St. 7 train express service is suspended.

The LIRR is accommodating NYCTransit Metrocard holders at no additional charge at Penn Station, Woodside, and Flushing-Main St.
See a station agent to receive a courtesy pass for continuing train or bus service.

For service to and from 34-St Hudson Yards, consider taking M34 SBS for crosstown service or traveling to Penn Station for E train service between Manhattan and Queens.

For service to/from 42 St-Times Sq, consider transferring between the 42 St Shuttle, Grand Central-42 St, the 4, 5, or 6 lines, and N or W lines for service to/from Queensboro Plaza, where Queens-bound 7 line service is available. 

For service to and from 5 Av-Bryant Park, consider taking the F train for service between Manhattan and Queens.

For service to/from Grand Central-42 St, consider transferring between the 4, 5, or 6 lines, and N or W lines for service to/from Queensboro Plaza, where Queens-bound 7 line service is available.

There is currently no 7 line service at Vernon Blvd-Jackson Av. Consider taking the nearby G line at 21 St. Here are directions: http://bit.ly/2LsNHsR

For Manhattan-bound service from Hunters Point Av, consider taking the nearby G line at 21 St to transfer to Manhattan-bound E or M service at Court Sq. Here are directions to 21 St: http://bit.ly/2kmLvXC As an alternative, take a Queens-bound 7 trains and transfer for continuing service at either Court Sq or Queensboro Plaza.
